Generations of kids loved the Fun House (1925-1971) with its giant wooden slide, undulating 50-foot walkway, rotating barrel, and fast-spinning disk. The old-fashioned fun house kept kids entertained for hours. In fact, at one point, it was nicknamed 'babysitting headquarters' because kids could stay and play all day for fifty cents! Do you have a favorite Fun House memory? 🤡🛝🪞#TBT

winter wonderland ❄️

The snow has left Lake Compounce looking like a winter wonderland!

Ever wondered what we do with our Christmas trees after Christmas Town? Well, here is your answer. 🌲

Fun Fact: Apart from serving as enrichment for Poppy & Thistle, the majority of our live trees are ground up and sprinkled into mulch throughout the park by our landscaping team!

Throwback to THEN vs NOW!

The castle that now sits in the center of Arrow's Adventure, formerly known as the Silver Slipper Castle, used to look a little different. When the original Santa's Village opened in the 1950s, the park was designed with a fairytale/storybook look in mind. The castle was open on both sides for children to play and run across the drawbridge. 

And do you recognize the colorful tables and stools by the castle? You can still find some around the park on the way to the Village Tree!

Wild Science and Junior Keepers are two of the awesome educational experiences happening this Saturday, Jan. 14!

🐒 In Wild Science, early-learning scientists “go wild” as they explore different parts of zoo life. Each class includes interactive discussions, inquiry-based activities, a visit from one of our animal ambassadors and more! This week, young scientists will look for critters that climb their way through the world. 🧗 Whether they use fingers, toes, tails or their nose, we want to discover how they do it.

🐼 Junior Keepers get to do what Happy Hollow's zoo crew does! Zoologists are scientists too, as you will learn when you practice your zookeeping skills. This week's theme is Extinction Exploration: Ice Age! 🧊 Junior Keepers will explore why some animals did not make it and what body features are the best in the extreme cold.

Visit happyhollow.org/hh-experience-programs/ to sign up!

The Gingerbread House Bakery & Sweet Shoppe is spreading s'more love!

Everyone knows of Marshmallow, the resident face painter and all-around artistic savant at Santa's Village. She is the Keeper of Color and the Magical Paint Brush Ealain, loves to sling paint wherever she can (even on faces!) and sees art in everything from Nature to the architecture of elves and man. 

Now you can try a new bakery item named just for her: Marshmallow's Peppermint S'More! With toasted marshmallows and crushed candy canes sandwiched between two delicious sugar cookies, this fun take on a campfire classic will leave you wanting s'more. Pick one up in St. Nick's Patio and Grille and the Bakery during your next visit!

Happy #MiloMonday! Although Milo the fennec fox doesn't like to spend time in the heavy rain, he doesn't mind getting his feet wet in order to look for food! This video shows Milo using a puzzle feeder, which is a form of enrichment that encourages his natural foraging behavior. 

ICYMI, Milo was recently transferred to Happy Hollow on the recommendation of the AZA Fennec Fox Species Survival plan and is currently completing a required quarantine period in Doc's Critter Care. Once he has cleared his quarantine and passed a final veterinary exam, he will move to his new home, the fennec fox habitat in the Zoo in the Hollow. Follow our social media for regular Milo updates!

Do you need chains? ⛓️

This is one of our most common questions we receive during the winter. Short answer - yes, drivers should always carry chains in their vehicles when driving to the mountains during the winter months. Caltrans may implement chain control at any given time depending on road conditions, so it's always best to be safe than stuck.

Click the link below to bookmark/save the Caltrans website for the most up-to-date road conditions. Select QuickMap Options ➡️ Road Conditions ➡️ Chain Controls for the current status. Plan ahead, take your time and see you soon!

Caltrans QuickMap: https://quickmap.dot.ca.gov/

Happy #MiloMonday! Milo is still doing well in quarantine 💛 It's apparent that he is very good at foraging for food! He's quick to search in boxes and puzzle feeders to find bits of meat 🥩 broccoli 🥦 or romaine lettuce 🥬 (another fave!) that we hide around his habitat to encourage natural behaviors.

ICYMI, Milo was recently transferred to Happy Hollow on the recommendation of the AZA Fennec Fox Species Survival plan and is currently completing a required quarantine period in Doc's Critter Care. Once he has cleared his quarantine and passed a final veterinary exam, he will move to his new home, the fennec fox habitat in the Zoo in the Hollow. Follow our social media for regular Milo updates!

VOCÊ JÁ CONHECE O RALLY?

Essa atração do #PlaylandInterlagos está fazendo o maior sucesso entre a criançada! 😁

No Rally os passageiros simulam um divertido passeio a bordo de carrinhos coloridos que giram, giram e giram sem parar, esparrando lama (de brincadeirinha) para todos os lados! 😄

Uma atração feita para as crianças, mas que também permite que os pais participem da brincadeira!

- Para ter acesso ao Rally as crianças precisam ter altura mínima igual ou superior a 0,90m. Confira na entrada da atração todas as informações e recomendações de segurança.
